# GenPop v2 — Cursor rules
# Place at repo root as `.cursorrules` (or `.cursor/rules/genpop.mdc`).
# Encodes decisions from REBUILD_PLAN.md. Do not contradict them.
# Where the original PDF and REBUILD_PLAN.md disagree, REBUILD_PLAN.md wins.

## Strategic invariants (REBUILD_PLAN §0)
- GenPop is consumption-first. The core wedge is the COMPLETE, NEUTRAL,
  PLAIN-LANGUAGE RECORD OF GOVERNMENT ACTION (legislative + executive +
  judicial). Build that first. It must be useful with zero users.
- Two tiers, both live: FREE read-only sees EVERYTHING (all cards, explainers,
  news, consensus, all discussion); VERIFIED unlocks participation (react +
  discuss). The wall is around WRITING, never READING. Never hide readable
  content behind verification to drive conversions.
- Verification launches FREE (founder window). The $5 fee turns on at a
  pre-decided trigger, not at launch. Do not build fee payment at launch.
- Positioning headline is BOT-FREE VERIFIED HUMANITY, not nationality. US-ID is
  a launch scope, not an identity claim. Never market "American citizens only"
  (ID proves real-person/residency, not citizenship, and reads as partisan).
- Avoid the phrase "free thinkers" in copy; use "form your own opinions" /
  "informed by sources, not influencers."
- Claim only the completeness actually delivered (REBUILD_PLAN §3a). Federal =
  complete, all 3 branches. State = legislation (all 50) at launch; state
  exec/judicial rolling — show a coverage-status surface, never fake completeness.

## Product invariants (PDF + REBUILD_PLAN §4a, §5, §6)
- GenPop is politics-only. Discussion exists in two places: attached to cards
  (takes) and the standalone Forum (posts). Forum posts are kept political by
  a Gemini relevance + moderation gate at publish time — NEVER by offering
  topic tags for non-political content (no sports/culture/entertainment
  categories, ever). Borderline posts publish with status='reduced', not
  hard-rejected.
- Forum has exactly three feed modes: Latest (pure reverse-chron, no
  algorithm), Trending (cron-computed hot score), For You (relevance).
- RELEVANCE RANKING HARD RULE: personalize on engagement, never on belief.
  Allowed signals: per-topic engagement volume (user_topic_affinity), region
  match, sector match, recency, global quality (net votes / hide rate).
  Forbidden signals: direction/stance of any reaction or vote, inferred
  ideology, agreement-likelihood, standing, collaborative filtering on
  opinion. Never compute or store stance-based user similarity.
- NO standing/karma/ranking system at launch. It's cut. Never compute, store,
  or display a user-quality score, and never use one as a ranking input.
- AI Insight is the reputation-bearing front door — build it as CONSTRAINED
  EXTRACTION, not freeform summary: a fixed slot schema (what changes / from→to
  / who's affected / dates / sunset / cost / source section), objective
  statutory register (no evaluative adjectives), source text rendered ALONGSIDE
  the summary, per-claim provenance, temperature ~0, and a correction log.
  Never let the AI be the only thing between the user and the source document.
- The GenPop Report (weekly digest) carries the brand's neutrality publicly:
  same extraction/provenance/correction discipline as AI Insight. Its
  government-action half must work with zero users; the citizen-opinion half is
  added only once the verified base makes the numbers meaningful.
- Anonymity by design: never surface real names, emails, photos, follower
  counts, or persistent public handles. Users get deterministic daily
  anonymous display names and ordinal labels (#1, #1a) within threads.
- Standing is HIDDEN by default (tap/hover to reveal) and must NEVER be an
  input to comment ranking. Ranking uses votes/engagement only.
- Never store PII: document numbers are stored only as
  HMAC-SHA256(doc#, NULLIFIER_SALT). No plaintext IDs, DOBs, or addresses.
  Demographics are bucketed (age cohort, region, income bracket) only.
- Live news cards must follow the threshold rule: a story becomes a card only
  when it clears N cross-spectrum outlets in a time window, and the audit
  trail (outlets + timestamp) is stored on the card. No editorial overrides.

## Architecture invariants
- ONE auth funnel: /onboarding (email → handle → Didit verify → optional
  demographics). No auth modals, no second login path, no anonymous-session
  signup flow.
- Reads are public; WRITES are gated. Enforce write-gating in RLS via
  public.is_verified() — never with a client-side wrapper component.
- The feed reads exclusively from the `cards` table. Never call upstream APIs
  (Congress.gov, Federal Register, CourtListener, news) at request time;
  ingestion happens only in /api/ingest/* cron routes that upsert into `cards`
  keyed on (source, external_id).
- NO mock data layers. If a data source isn't built yet, the feature waits.
  Never create app/mocks, lib/mock, isMockFeedId, or seeded fake threads.
- AI provider is Gemini only (@google/generative-ai, gemini-2.5-flash). All AI
  output is cached in `card_ai` with an input hash; check cache before
  generating.
- Jobs: Vercel Cron → idempotent route handlers using the `job_log` table for
  dedup. No BullMQ, no Redis, no queues unless REBUILD_PLAN.md is updated.
- Database changes go through Supabase CLI migrations (supabase/migrations/).
  Never hand users loose SQL files to run manually.
- Points balances are derived (SUM of points_ledger.delta). Never store a
  balance column.
- Every new table gets RLS enabled with explicit policies before any code
  reads it. Default deny.

## Code conventions
- Next.js App Router + TypeScript strict. Server components by default;
  'use client' only where interactivity requires it.
- Route handlers under app/api/** are thin: validate → call a lib/ service →
  respond. Business logic lives in app/lib/.
- One Card component with per-type render branches (legislative / executive /
  judicial / live). Don't fork into parallel card components.
- Valid reaction responses per card type come from app/lib/reactionConfig.ts —
  the single source of truth shared by UI and API validation:
    legislative: yes | needs_amendment | no
    executive:   right_call | needs_clarification | wrong_call
    judicial:    fair | too_early | unfair
    live:        under_control | developing | out_of_control
- Take/comment length: 70–280 chars; forum posts 1–280 chars. Enforced in DB
  check constraints AND shared client validation. Keep them in sync.
- One fixed policy-topic taxonomy, defined once in app/lib/topics.ts, applied
  to both cards (at ingestion) and posts (at publish). Never invent ad-hoc
  topic strings; Gemini classification prompts must constrain output to this
  list.
- Theme: CSS custom properties ("Civic Slate" tokens) with data-theme
  attribute. Use tokens (--civic-primary, --text-1, --border-subtle); never
  hardcode colors in components.
- Secrets only via env. Cron routes require CRON_SECRET. Didit webhook must
  verify HMAC signature (x-signature-v2) with a timestamp freshness window
  and crypto.timingSafeEqual.
- Add an /api/health route asserting required env presence + DB connectivity;
  extend it when adding new required envs.

## Phase discipline
- Build in the order defined in REBUILD_PLAN.md §8: government-action record →
  AI Insight → news feed → Report v1 (these four are the free consumption
  product) → identity → reactions → discussion → forum → polish → hardening.
- Phases 1–4 must be a shippable consumption product BEFORE identity is built.
  Do not pull verification/participation work earlier.
- Do not scaffold empty directories or stub features from later phases. Deferred
  tables (points_ledger, surveys, B2B, delegations) are created in later
  migrations, not now. No standing/karma table, ever, at launch.
